1.00	Simpletons	Jude the Obscure	Jude the Obscure, the last of Thomas Hardy's novels, began as a magazine serial and was first published in book form in 1895. The book was burned publicly by William Walsham How, Bishop of Wakefield, in that same year. Its hero, Jude Fawley, is a working-class young man who dreams of becoming a scholar. The other main character is his cousin, Sue Bridehead, who is also his central love interest. The themes in the novel revolve around issues of class, education, religion, and marriage. Hardy began making notes for the story in 1887.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Jude_the_Obscure_title_page.jpg/200px-Jude_the_Obscure_title_page.jpg
